          "payload": "node.web.detail"
        },
        "renderShape": {
          "kind": "markdown"
        },
        "markdown": "# Surface Authoring Walkthrough\n\nThis lesson is about the current surface model:\n\n1. author a graph\n2. declare surfaces in the declaration\n3. give each surface a stable payload\n4. let ports and portals consume what the target graph actually exposes"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "views-authoring-step-1",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Step 1",
      "position": {
        "x": 100,
        "y": -1040
      },
      "width": 480,
      "height": 240,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "identity": {
          "graphId": "tutorial-surface-authoring-walkthrough"
        },
        "markdown": "## Step 1: Author The Surface Nodes\n\nCreate the nodes that will render your surfaces.\n\nCommon choices:\n- a reader surface for opening the graph directly\n- a summary surface for ordinary consumption\n- a detail surface for richer context\n- an icon surface for compact display"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "views-authoring-step-2",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Step 2",
      "position": {
        "x": 620,
        "y": -1040
      },
      "width": 480,
      "height": 240,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "identity": {
          "graphId": "tutorial-surface-authoring-walkthrough"
        },
        "markdown": "## Step 2: Declare The Surfaces\n\nAdd each surface to `declaration.surfaces`.\n\nThat is what makes the surface discoverable.\n\nThe declaration should name the surface and point at the node that owns the rendering."
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "views-authoring-step-3",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Step 3",
      "position": {
        "x": 1140,
        "y": -1040
      },
      "width": 480,
      "height": 260,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "identity": {
          "graphId": "tutorial-surface-authoring-walkthrough"
        },
        "markdown": "## Step 3: Give Them Honest Payloads\n\nUse stable payload names like:\n- `node.web.summary`\n- `node.web.detail`\n- `node.web.icon`\n- `editor.web`\n\nNew data should describe the surface in the angular, declaration-first model you have been building everywhere else."
      }
    },
